# Manual SAML Request & Response Analysis 
📌 What This Project Demonstrates
This project walks through a full SAML 2.0 authentication flow, but instead of relying on a real application to generate SAML messages, you manually construct and send the SAMLRequest to Okta.
This gives you deep, protocol‑level understanding of how SAML works — the kind of insight IAM engineers rely on when debugging enterprise SSO issues.

You will:

- Build a SAML AuthnRequest by hand

- Encode it (Base64 + URL encoding)

Send it to Okta’s SAML Identity Provider (IdP)

Log in as the user

Capture and decode the SAMLResponse

Analyze the XML tags inside the SAML assertion

Observe how trust, signatures, and attributes work

This is the same process used when troubleshooting SAML integrations with Azure AD, Okta, ADFS, PingFederate, AWS IAM Identity Center, and more.
